The '''1990 [[Syracuse Orange football|Syracuse Orangemen football]] team''' represented [[Syracuse University]] in the [[1990 NCAA Division I-A football season|1991]] [[Division I (NCAA)#Football Bowl Subdivision|Division I-A]] [[college football]] season.
This season marked the end of two eras for Syracuse football. First, it was [[Dick MacPherson]]âs final year as head coach. He would leave to coach the [[1991 New England Patriots season|1991 New England Patriots]]. Second, it was the final season for Syracuse football as an independent. Starting with the [[1991 NCAA Division I-A football season|1991 season]], the [[Big East Conference]], of which Syracuse was a founding member, began sponsoring football competition.
